        <h2 id="free">Top 5 2020 Unrestricted Free Agents</h2>
        <h5>Posted Saturday, October 31, 2020</h5>
        
        <p>This free agency class might not have the biggest names out there, but will still prove to be important for the years to come.(Anthony Davis is not included in this list as he will almost certaintly be going back to The Lakers.)</p><br>
        <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64,"alt="Free Agency" width="250"><br>
        
        <h3>5. Davis Bertans (Washington Wizards)</h3>
        <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," width="250" />
        
<p>The Latvian Lazer is an absolute bucket from three point range appearing in the all star game as well as shooting a spectacular <em>42%</em> from deep on <strong>8.7</strong> attemps per game. With all this in mind it's safe to say that whatever team picks him up they'll be adding a valuble specislist to their roster.</p> <br>

<h3>4. Danilo Gallinari (Oklahoma City Thunder)</h3>
<img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Danilo Gallinari" width="250"> 
<p>Gallinari is a great team player that you can trust to get you <strong>15</strong> to <strong>20</strong> points on a consistant basis. Gallinari is another great three point shooter averaging just over <em>40%</em> from three last season. If one things for sure it's that Gallinari will be a great fit for any team he goes to thanks to his large frame and good shooting.</P> <br>
<h3>Goran Dragic (Miami Heat)</h3>
<img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Goran Dragic"width="250">
<p>The Dragon has been with the Heat franchise for the past 6 years and is a vocal point of the offense averaging <strong>16</strong> points and <strong>5</strong> assists per game last season. The heat are intrested in signing Giannis Antetokounmpo in the next free agency class, but will need cap space to do so making resigning a player that will ask for a  decent amoun tof money intresting. If Miami decides no to keep Dragic they still have two great young talents on small deals in Tyler Herro and Kendrick Nunn. It's Safe to say that Goran Dragic will certainly a home by next season.</p> <br>
<h3>2. Montrezl Harrell (Los Angeles Clippers)</h3>
<img src="data:image/jpeg;base64,"alt="Montrezl Harrell"width="250">
<p>The defending 6th Man of The Year is at the end of his contract and is expecting a bag this off season. The question is if the Clippers are willing to pay him. This past Playoff Run the Clippers were a big dissapointment with Harrell being one of the biggest reasons looking out of shape and the Clippers performing much better when he's off the court with Zubac's on instead. All this will make the outcome of Harrells free agency very intresting.</p> <br> 
<h3>1. Fred Vanvleet (Toronto Raptors)</h3>
<img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," width="250" >
<p>The 2019 NBA champion and undrafted gaurd has a big opportunity for serious money coming up. He's commonly seen as the best unrestricted free agent this time around with multiple teams looking to snag great piece for their team. The New York Nick are commenly seen as a team looking to take on Vanvleet this year. The Raptors are hoping to keep Freddie, but are also looking to make a splash in the following free agency leaving one question on the table. How much are the raptors willing to spend?
<h4>Top three teams intrested in Vanvleet</h4>

<h2 id="clippers">Clippers Next Step</h2>
<h5>Posted Monday, November 2, 2020</h5>
<img src="data:image/jpeg;base64,"alt="Paul George and Kawhi Leonard"width="250" >
<p>The Clippers had an extremly dissapointing playoff run after blowing a three to one lead against the Denver Nuggets well fighting for a spot in the Western Conference Finals. During this run the commenly agreed upon reason for the eventual downfall was the lack of chemistry the team had. The reason for the lack of chemistry is thought to have been the constant load managment from superstar Kawhi Leonard as well as the late arrival from both Harrell and Williams to the bubble. Another huge dissapointment was the performance of Paul George, he averaged 20 points on under 40% shooting from the feild. This year was supposed to be different than their previous playoff runs as the Clippers were considered favourites to win the title.</p><br>

<p>As you can see the their playoff runs have been nothing more than average and improvment is definitly needed for this Clippers franchise especially while trying to compete with it's LA  counterpart the Lakers. One option they could look into is aquiring a playmaker to run their offense, instead of just assuming two Superstars in George and Leonard can do it all. Another thing that could very well help them is more time, the season wasn't exacty a normal one with the lengthy hiatus and some injury time from Paul George especially after the general consensus was that their was a lack of chemistry. The last thing that will hopefully help them is their firing of long time head coach Doc Rivers that has blown more 3-1 leads than any other coach in history. With all that being said hopefully the so called curse that the Los Angeles Clippers have will finally be lifted this following season.</p><br><br><br>
